  "text": "The results indicated that the plasma concentration of phenylalanine, serine, carnitine and acetyl-L-carnitine in group B increased significantly compared with that in group I, while creatine, betaine, proline, tryptophan, tyrosine and C16: 0 LPC decreased significantly, which were related to the pathomechanism of depression. Among them, tryptophan, and C16:0 LPC have been discussed previously [CITATION_1] .",
